$ Oracle: Reservable columns
-

Reservable → development/databases/Oracle/objects/tables/columns[columns] were introducedin → development/databases/Oracle/Releases-and-versions/23c#ora23c-lock-free-reservations[23c].

A column can be reservable *if* the → development/databases/Oracle/SQL/data-types[data type] is numeric (→ development/databases/Oracle/SQL/data-types/number, integer and float)

Reservable columns cannot be → development/databases/Oracle/objects/indexes[indexed] and it's not possible to create → development/databases/Oracle/objects/tables/partitions[partitions] based on the value of reservable columns.

{ Misc

 *Reservable* is the official name for a feature that was originally called *escrow* column.

}
